  "market_context": "Analyst demonstrates a model-within-a-model on the oil triad where price manipulates the range low, displaces away leaving failure swings at retracement, and creates a fair value gap acting as a key level pointing to the opposing side of the range.",
  "key_observation": "Price retraces into the displacement fair value gap without forming SMT at the gap itself, but SMT confirmation appears via the correlated asset HO at the reversal point, validating a trade from the internal range (FVG) to the external range (opposing side).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price manipulated the range low on the oil triad.",
    "Step 2: Note the displacement away from the range low created a fair value gap and left failure swings at the retracement point.",
    "Step 3: Mark the fair value gap as the key level (internal range liquidity) and the opposing side of the range as the target (external range liquidity).",
    "Step 4: Wait for price to trade back into the gap as the reaction zone.",
    "Step 5: Confirm the reversal via SMT divergence with the correlated asset HO at the gap.",
    "Step 6: Enter on the following candles to trade the distribution away from the FVG into the opposing range high target."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When price creates failure swings and a fair value gap on displacement, the gap itself becomes a key level. SMT confirmation with a correlated asset at that gap validates an internal-to-external range trade toward the opposing side of the range.",
